Devious <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utyvenn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tyvenn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 12:52:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=577.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.broadpark.no/~bsvenhe/tyvimg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bards</span><hr size=1> Devious, Farm Golem wands, they dispell 4 buffs instant per click, and are rechargable, get a good bow, and practice your fletching skill so you can make 8dmg 100range arrows.<br>
<br>
<br>
Dispell the bard everytime selos kicks in, it costs money, but with jboots, or innate runspeed, you will most likely run faster, and a bard wont use jboots, caus he would rather wait for selos to kick in, if he was dispelled. (note, this will also dispell his dmg shields)<br>
<br>
If the bard gets away, use your bow. With primal bow and 8dmg arrows i shoot for 200+, combine this with duelist and fleeting quiver, and you got a very nice dmg output on range. <br>
Most rogues underestimate the use of bows, and duelist with bow in pvp.<br>
<br>
But vs a bard, if you dont wanna use poison, eggshaped pumice, or golem wands will work perfect.<br>
We used this tactic to take out our enemys bards in tot3. If a bard is dispelled immediatly when his selos kick in, hes like a mage without pet...DEAD<br>
<br>
Tyvenn S'vindel<br>
60 Assassin <br>
Champion of Rallos Zek<br>
