shoot for 210 with bow, 420dmg with duelist... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uclammorsz1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Clammor SZ1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 11:22:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=577.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bards</span><hr size=1> mr isn't the most important resist in high lvl solo bard pvp.  Basic strategy for bards revolves around 3 things:<br>
<br>
1)Dispel + bellow + melee<br>
against casters:  dispell away DS, sow, rune, hp buffs, resist buffs etc,  and melee with bellow to interupt whatever they think to cast.<br>
2)charm<br>
simple, pick a big mob (wurms are great for this) charm it, sick and pell off sow.  Snare is great if you can land it.<br>
3)OOS + dots<br>
occlusion of sound is an unresistabel mr/fr/cr debuff.  Our higher damage target dots are CR or FR and debuff the appropriate resist.  If a dot lands, it will more than likely debuff your resist enough to keep sticking.<br>
<br>
Things that kill bards:<br>
1)Dispell.  Dear lord I hate being pelled.  it messes up my buff order, I lose selo's and levi, and any potions or buff's I've picked up.  I love having run speed 3, but sow &gt; rs 3<br>
2)Rapture. unresistable mez. ugh.  it's often followed by ever resist debuff in the book, fetter, snare, and some big ass nukes.<br>
<br>
Best advice for rogues is to get fr/cr/mr into the 120's atleast.  dots will stick at 70 in the resist nearly every time, so you need to have near 100 after OOS.<br>
<br>
